  "description": "Ancient Mesoamerican scrying: obsidian mirrors were used to see into darkness, to glimpse what could not be directly observed. High depth (0.88) and activated formant intensity (0.70) give the tone its dark reflectivity — you hear the room as much as the note. Filter at 0.6 keeps warmth without obscuring the glass-like character. Dense, dark, with an interior glow.",
